Fire destroyed property worth N1.5 million Monday night in Kafanchan main market, Jema’a Local Government Area of Kaduna State. The Chairman of the traders’ association in the area, Alhaji Salisu Idris, told Daily Trust yesterday that 14 shops were destroyed. “It’s a huge loss and quite devastating, he said. He also called on the government to come to the aid of the traders. The council’s chairman, Peter Danjuma Averick, sympathised with the traders and promised to help them. 